Program: Discovery
Title: European space mapping
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwp4
Last Broadcast Date: 13 May 1996
The European Space Agency approves a satellite to map cosmic microwaves. The European Space Agency satellite has a launch date of 2003 and by mapping cosmic microwaves will find out where the galaxies came from and could even help provide an age for the universe. Presenter: Roland Pease.